default19default Large contracts excluding the VCS have been most visible in the Government’s flagship Work Programme. Organisations wishing to deliver one of 40 prime contracts had to display an annual turnover of at least £20 million and the financial capacity to deliver large contracts that require significant cash-flow. Consequently only three charities now act as a prime contractor. The 21 prime contracts for the 
defaultMoJ’s
default ‘Transforming Rehabilitation’ 
defaultexpects
default organisations to have an annual turnover of between £6-36 million. 
